@20710 = ~О Тенях над Соубаром:

Поскольку уже стало общепринято добавлять описательный текст к модам, то я тоже решил написать что-то в этом роде. Итак:

Прежде всего, я Биссон, создатель SoS. Хочу поблагодарить всех за то, что играете в мой маленький мод (правда, 300 Мб не так уж и мало) и надеюсь, что он вам нравится. Должен сказать, что мне очень понравилось работать над модом, несмотря на все проблемы, с которыми я столкнулся. У меня ушло два винчестера и намного больше сд-дисков на создание резервных копий, и все равно я умудрился стереть область кладбища и квест по ограблению Лавки Искателей Приключений. Конечно, восстановить все было не так уж сложно, но я потерял две или три недели.

Second, I realize that the main quest of the adventure isn't really spectacular by any means, I mean, how original is a bunch of bandits attacking a town?  Well, be that as it may, I think I did a pretty good job with most of the scripting individual parts to all the quests.  For example, I truly enjoy scripting the behind the scenes stuff, like Selence and her attempts at pickpocketing.  Scripting Hellblades to work almost just right was a trick too, and it's a lot of fun to see it work the way it was intended, if not a bit mechanical.  So I hope you get a chance to sit back and watch some of those things.

Next, I think I want to say something about the creation itself.  None of this would have been at all possible without the indirect efforts of so many people.  Most of those are the members of TeamBG.  Ken Baker, TL, Cat, Gorin, Gaelion and PatternStorm, gafman, Theo, Manveru, Maltanar, and Jon.  Forgive me if I left anyone out... and tell me to add it in a patch!  Without their skill at making the number of programs I've used for Shadows Over Soubar, you wouldn't be reading this now as I would never have attempted to even begin such a task.  So, with the greatest appreciation to those programmers, I say thank you and well done.  

Finally, as I am writing this text, Shadows of Soubar's completion draws ever nearer.  What I had thought would be about 150MB of an expansion with only about 40 extra areas, turned into about 300MBs and close to 100 extra areas; 3 brand new ones.  What I had thought would be a four or five month project just took up the last nine months of my life.  Hey, I could have had a baby in that amount of time.  No, wait, I can't have a baby, but I had a lot of fun trying during the last nine months, and that has nothing to do with this expansion, if ya know what I mean, (wink wink, nudge nudge).

Seriously though, I am quite pleased at the result.  Shadows Over Soubar is an accomplishment of mine, and with you all playing it, perhaps it will be another successful accomplishment.

Thank You,
All My Best,
God Bless,

CBisson

